Trinity::

She finally stopped crying, but still felt bad for the loss of her 
family. "Yeah, let's get out of here."  She tried hard not to start 
crying again. But she couldn't help it.  Even though she had nothing 
to do with the death of her family or the fall of the ship, her 
childlike mind made her feel responcable for it all in some way. She 
felt like it was all her fault.  Like she was the reason all the bad 
things happened that caused the deaths of the family.
